Boilerplate HTML with Custom Styles
This project provides a simple boilerplate HTML file with custom styling using CSS.

Features
Custom Styles: Utilizes CSS for custom styling, including font imports, button styles, and hover effects.
Responsive Design: The HTML template is designed to be responsive and adapt to different screen sizes.
FontAwesome Integration: Includes FontAwesome for adding icons to elements.
How to Use
Clone the repository to your local machine or download the index.html and style.css files.
Open the index.html file in your web browser.
Customize the content of the HTML file as needed.
Modify the style.css file to adjust the styling according to your preferences.
Add additional HTML elements or stylesheets as required for your project.
Project Structure
index.html: Contains the boilerplate HTML structure with custom styles.
style.css: Defines the custom styles for the HTML elements.
README.md: Provides information about the project, its features, and how to use it.
Customization
Content: Customize the content of the HTML file to fit your project needs.
Styling: Modify the CSS styles in the style.css file to change the appearance of the HTML elements.
FontAwesome Icons: Replace the FontAwesome icon class (fa fa-arrow-right) with any other FontAwesome icons available.
